{{Infobox astronaut | name = Konstantin Anatolyevich Valkov | image = | image_size = | type = [[Russian Federal Space Agency|RKA]] Cosmonaut | status = Retired | nationality = Russian | birth_date ={{Birth date and age|1971|11|11}} | birth_place = [[Kamensk-Uralsky]], Russia | occupation = | rank = [[Colonel]] | selection =[[List of astronauts by selection#1997|1997 TsPK Cosmonaut Group]] | time = | mission = | insignia = |}}
'''Konstantin Anatolyevich Valkov''' ({{lang-ru|Константин Анатольевич Вальков}}; November 11, 1971- ) is a Russian former [[Astronaut|Cosmonaut]]. He was selected as part of the TsPK-12 Cosmonaut group in 1997.<ref name="sf">{{cite web|title=Konstantin Valkov|url=http://www.spacefacts.de/bios/cosmonauts/english/valkov_konstantin.htm|publisher=[[Spacefacts]]|accessdate=31 October 2010}}</ref><ref name="astronautix">{{cite web|title=Valkov |url=http://www.astronautix.com/astros/valkov.htm |publisher=[[Astronautix]] |accessdate=31 October 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080725060120/http://www.astronautix.com/astros/valkov.htm |archivedate=July 25, 2008 }}</ref>
==Biography== ===Early life and education===
Valkov was born in [[Kamensk-Uralsky]], [[Sverdlovsk Oblast]], Russia on November 11, 1971. In 1994, he graduated from [[Barnaul Higher Military Air School of Pilots]] and subsequently became a Colonel in the [[Russian Air Force]].<ref name="sf"/>
===Cosmonaut career===
Valkov was selected as part of the TsPK-12 group of cosmonauts to train at the [[Yuri Gagarin Cosmonaut Training Center]] in 1997. He then completed basic training in 1999.<ref name="sf"/> He retired without flying in space in 2012.<ref name="sf"/>
